original_title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue Extension - West Broadway N. Lispenard
text:
Sixth Ave. Extension and West Broadway, at a point slightly north of Lispenard, showing a triangular space bounded by same, with Canal Street on the far side. Across the roofs of the buildings on the latter thoroughfare appears the tower atop St. Alphonsus R. C. Church. The photographer is viewing northward.

May 2, 1938.

P. L. Sperr.

Sixth Avenue, north from Lispenard Street. The open area seen is at Canal Street. Buildings to the right are No's. 1 and 3 Lispenard Street, same being opposite the New York Telephone Company building and where the photographer is standing.

July 12, 1939

P. L. Sperr

West Broadway (right) and Sixth Avenue (left), north from Lispenard Street, showing prominently the triangular plot at this convergence. Forming the far side of same is Canal Street. North of this main cross-town thoroughfare appears St. Alphonsus R. C. Church.

View 1: March 19, 1939
View 2: May 19, 1939

P. L. Sperr

West Broadway (right) and Sixth Avenue (left), north from Lispenard Street, showing prominently the triangular plot at this convergence. Forming the far side of same is Canal Street. North of this main cross-town thoroughfare appears St. Alphonsus R. C. Church.

View 1: March 19, 1939
View 2: May 19, 1939

P. L. Sperr

West Broadway, north from Lispenard Street, showing this thoroughfare subsequent to the de- molition of the Sixth Avenue "El" line.

To the right are 3-story buildings at the N.E. corner of Lispenard Street. Running diagonally across the foreground is the Sixth Avenue Extension and from which the photographer is viewing. Canal Street is behind the gas station at the triangular plot formed by the convergence of Sixth Avenue and West Broadway. Upon the west side of the latter and north of Canal Street is St Alphonsus R.C. Church.

Note in the distance the vague outlines of the Empire State Building and the distinctive apartment structure, No. 1 Fifth Avenue.

July 12, 1939

P. L. Sperr

West Broadway, north from Lispenard Street, showing this thoroughfare subsequent to the de- molition of the Sixth Avenue "El" line.

To the right are 3-story buildings at the N.E. corner of Lispenard Street. Running diagonally across the foreground is the Sixth Avenue Extension and from which the photographer is viewing. Canal Street is behind the gas station at the triangular plot formed by the convergence of Sixth Avenue and West Broadway. Upon the west side of the latter and north of Canal Street is St Alphonsus R.C. Church.

Note in the distance the vague outlines of the Empire State Building and the distinctive apartment structure, No. 1 Fifth Avenue.

July 12, 1939

P. L. Sperr

West Broadway, at Lispenard Street between Canal and Walker Streets,
looking south.
P. L. Sperr  July 12, 1939
